__label__Jaipur,Rajasthan this photo might represent the scenario for every twenty-something out there with a multitude of options and passions, but only two feet to work with.

perhaps in another life, on the 7th day, god would've siesta'd, but still had time to create us with 6 arms and legs to keep up with our 72-tab browser mindset.

i admire those who got to 80 years old and tried their hand at 3 different careers, fulfilling 3 different areas of their lives.

i don't think we're meant to do the same thing every day for the next 60 years, call it a life, and die.

we're all so talented and too dynamic to have just a single story written about our lives.

stepping out on faith is scary. but what's scarier is the amount of people that take their dreams to the grave with them.

because they sat around waiting on their parents' approval. on the perfect amount of savings. on their partner's situation to get better.

there's nothing selfish about pursuing a life that makes you wildly excited about monday mornings.

anybody who tries to tell you otherwise isn't the kind of energy you should be surrounding yourself with.

it's time to stop seeking approval from those with entrepreneurial minds but an elementary work ethic.

i've said it before and i'll say it again. our dreams are all different, but our need for fulfillment is the same.

when was the last time you did something that truly made you feel worthy?

worthiness isn't birthed overnight. and self-confidence might be the longest and most unstable road in the world. but anything worth having in life requires working towards it daily.

financial stability. a happy marriage. a healthy heart and body.

so maybe you're stuck in the middle of a crossroad but you're on the verge of turning your whys into why nots.

the universe always conspires in your favor when your work ethic meets it halfway.

here's to my fellow dreamers. may you forever continue to be anything but normal 🤘🏾 photo credit | @dakotaadan

__label__Havana,Cuba because @dante.vincent and i decided to visit cuba by the most legal means open to americans when we booked our trip 6 months ago, we chose a sanctioned photography tour with @harryfisch.correo. harry encouraged us to be bold in getting to know cuban people, to approach them and ask them for photos. at first, i felt timid despite my decades of experience behind the camera but as our hours & days in havana wore on, i realized moments like this were my very favorite. even better than the colorful cars and the crumbling architecture, that i'd so looked forward to before arriving -- was the sense that we were connecting with what *actually* makes cuba special. it's the people. so passionate, so quick to smile at you, so curious to know your story & to share their own, so open to sharing what precious little they have so that you leave wanting only to return again. and soon! sure enough, that's what danté and i want to do: return. this handsome local smiled at me, inviting me to take his photo while we were walking in a very local section of older havana and though he had to continue working instead of sharing his story, his is only one of perhaps two dozen or more faces that i could share with you! #facesofcuba
also, this week on the @circa39miami & @palmshotelmiami feeds i'm sharing photos of the experience danté & i are having here in florida  before we finally return home to nyc. get your dose of palm trees and ocean views there since that's not something we found in cuba 😉🌴

__label__PlanetEarth our pain can be our greatest teacher. it leads us to places we would never go on our own.
.
i’m still in ecuador at an ayahuasca/san pedro retreat but i wanted to share a few thoughts from one of the many insights i’ve learned while working with these two plant medicines. this particular retreat center not only focuses on your own personal healing but our healing as a community. after hearing so many stories from my new family here, it’s reaffirmed that our pain is also our beauty. the level you allow yourself to feel and accept the pain from your past or present is in direct relation to the level of joy you feel.
.
don’t be afraid of feeling pain. it’s only temporary. be grateful for it as it can teach you some of life’s greatest lessons. it also gives you the capacity to hold a space for someone else who might be in pain and give them the opportunity to heal.
.
i can’t wait to share more thoughts soon! i love you all and hope you realize how beautiful you are. 😘

__label__SouthernProvince,SriLanka one of the questions we get a lot is; does it rain all the time during the monsoon season? answer is no. we can get some heavy rains in the beginning but then it usually clears up and you have sunny days with the occasional showers. sometimes it rains during the afternoons, which leaves the jungle green and lush. personally this is our favorite time of the year. it’s less crowded, you can often get the whole beach to yourself. 🙌🏽

__label__Bali,Indonesia so grateful and happy to feel like i’m almost back to my “normal” self! for anyone who doesn’t know me, i take photos, work, and go on adventures every day, without a day off, and this week i didn’t do any of that until today due to an accident and anxiety attack that put me in the hospital. 😭
.
i know people give social media a bad name sometimes, but honestly, this has been my best form of therapy! i read and took all of your comments seriously on my last post, and i feel like it was your support and suggestions that got me through the weird sudden trauma-anxiety i experienced earlier this week following my bus accident. (also randomly running into a friend from college who helped distract me and also take this pic helped too!)
.
this life of traveling full time, also as your career, and always public, has its perks for sure, but i’ll never hide the behind the scenes aspect of it which involves accidents and heath-well being!
.
i’m grateful now more than ever to acknowledge that i’ve made myself such a strong, motivated, hard-working, open-minded, and empathetic person through travel, and grateful for the opportunity to show others how much it can change your life as well!
.
so here’s to wishing everyone a warm, colorful, energized weekend, i love you all! 💖
.

__label__Antarctica at first glance, this doesn’t look like such an uncommon photo, right? just some birds circling over an iceberg in antarctica. but like most things in antarctica, there’s much more below the surface. these birds are really special and beautiful birds called snow petrals, found almost exclusively in the icy realm of the white continent. they are petite birds with snow white feathers, coal black eyes and beak, and bluish grey feet. they tend to flutter about more than fly. to see one up close is a real treat, as they are stunningly beautiful, resembling little angels in a way. but in many trips to antarctica i’ve never seen so many in one place at one time. this sighting is quite rare, as far as i can tell. the lack of color coupled with the ice and large flock of one of my favorite birds in the world took my breath away. it was a beautiful sight that turned out to be one of my favorite sightings on recent expeditions. to know that these birds congregate like this, and are probably doing this exact thing right now, makes me smile. antarctica is magical. 
#onassignment @natgeoimagecollection @natgeo @natgeofineart @natgeoexpeditions #nationalgeographicorion #antarctica

__label__Stockholm,Sweden do you want to change, but don't know where to begin? in my coaching work, i've noticed that people who reach out to me want to make a change in their lives... but feel completely stuck on how to get there.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
change (or lack thereof) starts with our beliefs. we each have a set of beliefs, and they sometimes limit us. for example: you believe you are not good enough. you believe that life is unfair. you believe people are not trustworthy. and so on.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
when we rigidly subscribe to our beliefs, everything we experience will affirm or deny those beliefs. your world becomes a place where you are not good enough, life is unfair, and people are not trustworthy.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
it doesn't have to be that way.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
change begins when we choose to let our beliefs go and see the world for what it is.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
letting go of your beliefs does not mean you don't have them. it just means you are not enslaved by them.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
when we recognize that our beliefs are subjective and a result of our experience, we can then choose who we want to be. we make choices based on the present moment rather than the conditioning of our past.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
it all depends on what's more important to you - changing your life, or sticking to your beliefs regardless of how they limit you?
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
📷: @andytrace.uk

__label__TourEiffel ever since i started travel writing five years ago i've wanted to do a post on what it costs for a family to go to disneyland, and then show where else in the world they could go for the same money. there's nothing wrong with disneyland per se, but the world is amazing, and kids gain so much from being exposed to it! 
my post went live last night and already has thousands of views and a lot of great comments. i love hearing that so many people have gone to disneyland and disney world and thought the same thing - where else could all of these families go for this much money? the post's at babbo.com/disneyland and is linked from my profile. let me know your thoughts too. disneyland or the world? or both? 
and yes, one of my suggestions is paris - pictured. you could head over from virtually anywhere in the us in june and spend six nights and still spend less than you would at disneyland.

__label__Dubai,UnitedArabEmirates the united arab emirates is such an impressive country. it was founded in 1971 - let that sink in! and now the uae boasts the tallest building, biggest malls and largest markets✨ in the world ✨, as well as a slew of incredibly impressive architecture, mosques, beaches, resorts and more. they have a second atlantis, the only other location of the lourve, the rain room, the world’s largest race track, etc etc etc. it’s home to people that represent over 200 nationalities - the government does not issue citizenship, only residencies, but they welcome all nationalities. and little pockets of those nationalities can be found all over the city - including american “culture.” they had a chili’s, texas roadhouse, shake shack, red lobster and more in their malls. 😂🇺🇸🗽
what country were you most impressed by when you learned more about their history?

__label__Vancouver,BritishColumbia 15 jan: vancouver 
today was a hard day to get motivated... vancouver is the last stop on this incredible adventure for me and i was not really feeling ready to come home and face reality just yet! instead i wanted to lock myself in my hotel and pretend like that return ticket didn't exist 😏 
the downside of travelling alone means on days like today, no one is there to help inspire you to get moving so it was afternoon before i ventured outdoors into beautiful (mild) vancouver... temps that didn't have a minus in front of them - unheard of 😂
but what i did do was explore on foot, hit up the information centre to build a plan for tomorrow and finished my day with a double vodka/hard lemonade cocktail ... it was the type of day i needed and that made everything ok 💙

__label__NewYork,NewYork this is leticia (@ticiaripa). her dream is to incorporate her passion of travel and helping people into her career and journey in life. she also happens to be my best friend.

whenever she comes over, we have a routine that extends as far back as our 13 years of friendship; she watches me meander from drawer to drawer, looking for the perfect outfit to wear to our next adventure. frozen with indecision, i ask her which outfit i should select before even trying it on. her answer is the same, every time: “just try it.”

by repeating that simple mantra over the years, leticia taught me a lesson that extends far beyond outfits: it is far better to try something we are curious about and be unafraid to change if it doesn’t fit, than to remain stagnantly suspended in indecision. 

let go of the irrational fear that something will go wrong before even knowing what it’ll look like. have faith that your intuition is guiding you in the right direction. just try it. #thenomadsoasisproject #celinnesoasis #followyourdream

p.s. for those of you wondering, the outfits turn out fabulous 😛

__label__CapeTown,WesternCape creative constipation 💩
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
i’ve admittedly been a bit disconnected mentally and physically from ig for the past few weeks. like clockwork, this “constipation” kicks in every year towards year end. i physically can’t bring myself to pick up a camera, let alone pose for one. i feel like i have nothing interesting to say and simply don’t have the energy to create or share. • i started to realize that mayyybe sharing 5 blog posts weekly, daily ig stories, weekly youtube videos, daily ig posts, and daily twitter, facebook and pinterest posts would reduce my normally overflowing jar of creativity to crumbs. (guess that’s not all that surprising, is it?)
•
when i come home between trips, i nurture my mental and physical health by slowing down, developing a routine, and binge watching mindless tv. i have to balance my highly-overstimulating lifestyle with simple pleasures. • just like my mental and physical health, i’ve found that i also need to nurture my creativity. when i’m feeling creator’s block, i distance myself from my normal routine. i stop posting. i stop sharing. i stop shooting. i start reading. i start baking. i learn a new skill. i seek anything creative that is totally unrelated to what i ‘normally’ do. (i even started a “home sweet africa” cross-stitch set lol!)
•
einstein called this act “combinatory play” — opening one mental channel by dabbling in another. when creativity is your job, the stakes are high. you can’t always be creative just for the fun of it. you have to post daily, ‘beat the algorithm’ and deliver ‘epic’ content constantly. by exploring new creative outlets, it keeps my inspiration in motion, but relieves me of the pressure i put on myself. i spend my time trying things that are ok for me to not be good at, and i start to slowly refill my creative jar. • in true “instagram inspiration” form, i shared this nugget of self-awareness on a pretty picture that’s completely unrelated to the message. but, i hope that because of it, some of you relate to it and seek out that soul nourishing creative break you also need. • more pretty pictures soon! promise

non è ancora cresciuto.

e quello

non te l'ho ancora detto (nazım hikmet) 🥀 la plus belle mer: n'a pas encore été traversée.

nos plus beaux jours: nous n'avons pas encore vu. et les plus belles paroles que je voulais te dire, je ne l'ai pas encore dit. (nazim hikmet) 🥀el más bello de los mares

einen schönen montag ihr lieben 💜 ich hoffe es geht euch gut? heute gibt es von mir ein bild vom nymphenburgerschloss. 🏰 ich muss gestehen, dass ich mittlerweile das 4. jahr hier in der gegend wohne und es noch nicht einmal geschafft habe, dort hinzugehen. 🤪 ups. ich muss sagen, dass es auf alle fälle einen besuch wert ist, vor allem der schlosspark ist so groß und schön. ich denke im sommer als auch im winter 😍 man denkt nicht, dass man in einer großstadt ist wenn man dort ist! auf alle fälle eine große empfehlung von mir, wer einmal nach münchen kommt 👍🏼 wer kennt es und war auch schon dort? ☺️ würde mich mal interessieren? 
ich hoffe ihr habt heut euren tag gut rumbekommen. ich merke immer noch das ich etwas angeschlagen bin & freue mich jetzt auf den feierabend 🤧🙈
•
happy monday 💜💜💜

__label__Istanbul,Turkey “sultan ahmed” aka “blue mosque”  is a historic mosque located in istanbul, turkey. it was constructed between 1609 and 1616 during the rule of ahmed i. its külliye contains ahmed's tomb, a madrasah and a hospice. the decorations include verses from the qur'an, many of them made by seyyid kasim gubari, regarded as the greatest calligrapher of his time. and has over 200 stained glass windows. it is now one of the most visited sites in istanbul. 🕌😇♥️

__label__Budapest,Hungary the sun rises and sets on both good and evil. which makes each new day a blessing, as our tomorrows are never guaranteed.

i pray we as a whole continue to cultivate and focus on the good, the pure, and the magic in this world.

especially during times we allow the bad to cloud our judgment and let us think our good hearts are the minority.

my heart goes out to everyone in nice today, and it was such a relief to see my friends there, one by one, mark themselves as safe on facebook.

we also had a @busabouteurope crew there yesterday who've thankfully all been accounted for.

love and light to everyone today.

we also say goodbye to budapest and hello to croatia for the ultra music festival this weekend.

thankful for continued journey mercies throughout my travels and i long for the day we can wake up without a new hashtagged city or person to mourn over 💔

__label__Taipei,Taiwan 感情是兩個人的事，
不是誰單方面就可以決定誰的人生。

也許是家裡有一部分的不完美，
才讓我在談感情的時候，
有那麼一點點自卑，
總覺得對方會不會因為我哪裡的不夠好，
嫌棄我，離開我，
後來在經歷了這麼多個年頭，
才發現真正的愛情是許了承諾依舊不離不棄，
見過你邋遢的樣子卻喜歡那份慵懶，
見過你害怕的樣子卻喜歡你的可愛。

第一次和你一起過年，
謝謝你知道媽咪孤單所以選擇跟我們一起吃年夜飯，
謝謝你的家庭給你最大的自由，
讓寂寞的我們在這樣的年節有人陪伴，
謝謝你的所有退讓還有支持著我往前，
謝謝遇見你以後的人生，
彩色的讓我飛上天。

新的一年，我會繼續好好的賴著你，
永遠愛你，我的小寶寶。

__label__Bangalore,India looking out.

it is often a dilemma i've found myself in: to find a perfect picture, to decide whether to post a picture or not, to decide the worth of a photograph or a bunch of words to the likes of the audience.

rare a realisation that you never really understand what the artist tries to convey over a their art - we are all bound by our vision of the world. all you can is relate.

and i've probably figured out that you cannot let the mess you are made up of conform to the moulds offered by the world.

there's nothing quite striking about this picture, nor do we have plato lending a quote for the caption; all we do is an overprocessed picture filling out a random feed.

here's to being the unique kind of weird you are. here's to finding beauty in everything and not meaning.

__label__SouthernProvince,SriLanka anyone felt homesick? 🙋🏻‍♀️
.
.
for the last few days i’ve been seriously ill with the flu, and stuck in bed with a fever. i called my best friend back home in tears. i was homesick. i missed my bed. i missed my friends, my family. i missed my pups. i missed the comfort of home, mostly because i was so uncomfortable 🤧🤒
.
.
i have been on the road 10 months and this was the very first time i even thought about buying a flight home. like, actually thought about the fact that i’m free to do it, and if i miss home i can go back anytime. i could be home tomorrow if i really wanted. but that really wasn’t the answer ✈️
.
.
i think missing home while traveling is a lot like missing an ex boyfriend. you crave the familiar when you are sick, or sad. its your security blanket. it sounds great in theory, and it would provide momentary happiness, but soon you’d remember why you moved on 🌏
.
.
so no offense to my home or my ex boyfriends, but i’m not coming back anytime soon! after all discomfort means growth, and thats why i’m out here anyway 🙏🏽
.
.
#travelgram #vegantravel #srilanka #blogger #travel

__label__MainBeach as promised here is my macro work from this morning. doesn't look like much does it? surprisingly this is a pretty hard shot, macro specialists have my full respect. here i used the nikon d600 with a 60mm tamron macro lens. on the tripod i manually focused on the drop using a precision focusing technique. my settings were iso 100, f29, 1/13 and i used an external flash on manual 1/64. (hand held) even after all that it's not perfect, but i'm still happy. i'll have to do some more indoor macro soon for practice. lol

__label__Petra,Ma`An,Jordan hope you forgive me for the lag in posts my friends. i pretty much worked myself to the ground towards the end of 2018 and ever since i got back to nyc at the beginning of the new year, i’ve been taking it easy and  enjoying the slow start to the year with the pleasures of simple things like catching up with friends, making new ones and cuddling with my cat 😄 as dreamy as full-time travel sounds in theory, stability and comfort are just as vital and i‘ve never felt more at peace and happy ever since i took the time to slow down a bit 🥰 i’ve learned how important it is to pause and to listen to my mind, body and heart. they sometimes carry the answers to the questions we’re often stumped by, if we only take the time to listen. but! i’ll be back on the road soon, just spacing my travels out a bit and enjoying my base in nyc! first stop: nashville 🇺🇸 recommendation welcome! and message me if you’re in town during valentine’s day weekend 😬

__label__PhiPhiIslands for the next few days, i'll be partnering with @wyndhamrewards to share some of the most "magical moments" in my travels!
starting tuesday, @wyndhamrewards wants to see your magical travel moments.
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
i can't believe it's been almost 4 years ago since i sat here looking out over ko phi phi in thailand. this was my first ever solo trip. i remember sitting anxiously in the airport in melbourne as i awaited my flight to thailand.

a million emotions ran over me as i questioned every aspect of my decision to travel southeast asia on my own. "would i be safe?" "what if nobody spoke english?" "what if i was lonely?" i sat here, a week after arriving in thailand, feeling all of the scared and worrisome emotions wash away with the tide. i knew my life would never be the same and committed to sharing my own story in hopes that it would inspire others to take the same leap of faith in life.

and so began the journey of the blonde abroad…

__label__Singapore when we began our around-the-world #sliceofadventure project with @oroweatbread, i had no idea what kind of sandwiches we would make at our destinations – except for singapore! years ago i saw that singapore’s ice cream sandwiches were made with a block of ice cream placed into a slice of bread. so i wanted to make it happen! i took a slice of oroweat’s organic rustic white to an ice cream cart near the historic cavenagh bridge and asked the seller to use my bread for the ice cream sandwich. no problem! i chose red bean ice cream – one of my favorite flavors, and i rarely see it in the us. it was great! seriously – if you have some oroweat organic and some ice cream at home, try combining them and let me know what you think!

__label__Prague,CzechRepublic letztes jahr ende märz waren wir in prag. 5 tage bloß und das wetter war auch nicht sonderlich toll, aber es hat sich gelohnt - wir haben das beste gulasch unseres lebens gegessen! an einem verregneten abend, außerhalb der touribereiche, in einer kleinen kneipe wo niemand englisch sprechen konnte. weltklasse gulasch, ich sag es euch! wir haben uns vorab günstige flüge rausgesucht und haben im #hotelinternationalprague geschlafen. nicht ganz zentral, aber ordentlich und ein super preis-leistungsverhältnis inklusive frühstück. alles in allem kommt man in prag sehr günstig rum. wir haben natürlich sie üblichen hot-spots abgeklappert, die karlsbrücke, die tanzenden häuser und die burg. wir sind aber auch viel einfach nur rumgelaufen, haben uns kleine läden und lokale angeschaut. prag ist wunderschön! heißer tipp: ein besuch lohnt sich besonders außerhalb der hauptreisezeit im sommer. dadurch das prag relativ günstig ist, verschlägt es gerade zur karlsbrücke im sommer tausende täglich. abgesehen kann man außerhalb der hauptreisezeit wirklich schnapper bei den flügen machen. prag ist definitiv einen besuch wert!

__label__Havana,Cuba one of many favorite days in havana 🇨🇺 spent cruising around the city’s streets and neighborhoods with a charming cuban driver in a classic 1963 chevy under blue skies. • • • • • • • • • • • • • • • • 
he had english music playing which i presume he thought i’d enjoy as a tourist until i asked him to play his favorite cuban songs. he smiled from ear to ear and put on salsa music 🎶 which he ‘danced’ to while driving. ‘do you know how to dance 💃🏻 salsa?’ he asked. ‘not even close’ i answered almost embarrassed 😬. ‘ahh mija you can’t come to cuba and not learn. i’ve been dancing since i was born. i will teach you.’

__label__Paris,France ✈️🇫🇷
como é voar com air france!!!!
observação: sempre que vou para europa, 
vou de air france.. exceto quando vou para espanha( que vou de iberia pois o voo é direto para madrid)
**
📍cada passageiro da classe econômica tem direito a levar duas malas de 23kg e uma mala de mão de 12kg, além de um acessório.
**
📍o check-in do voo só pode ser feito 30h antes.
**
📍não acho o avião desconfortável. há espaço suficiente para as pernas.
**
📍em cada lugar tem o cobertor, travesseiro e fones de ouvido. 
depois eles passam servindo uma toalhinha molhada para limpar as mãos e também espirrando um spray com um cheirinho maravilhoso.
**
📍durante todo o tempo os comissários de bordo checam se os passageiros estão  com cinto de segurança quando o comandante liga o alerta. 
achei bem eficiente 👏🏻👏🏻

__label__NewZealand ich. atme. ein. es ist dieses gefühl. 
wie nenn ich es? geborgenheit, zufriedenheit, sicherheit….. nein. das trifft es nicht. es ist wohl eine ganze reihe von gefühlen. oder nein – es ist dieser moment.  nicht die momente davor, wenn du mich anlächelst wenn du zur tür reinkommst. nicht der augenblick wenn du mich küsst oder wir uns nach einem streit vertragen. das ist der moment. wenn ich abends neben dir liege. ankommen. minze, etwas süßes & etwas unerklärliches. ich atme ein. es ist perfekt. du zeigst mir, dass es tatsächlich diesen menschen gibt, der deine geheimnisse kennt, der dich liebt – für deine fehler, deine tränen, deine freude, deine entscheidungen….. du zeigst mir, dass zuhause sein tatsächlich bedeutet anzukommen, zu schreien, zu lachen, zu tanzen, zu lieben. dass es kein ort ist – sondern wahrhaftig die person neben mir. und dazu musst du nicht einmal etwas sagen. du musst nur neben mir liegen und in dem moment, in dem ich einatme – weiß ich es
☀️

__label__Paris,France i was in paris yesterday to kick off a project my team was doing with another team in our paris office.
.
i remember being so anxious the first few times i had to run workshops like this. always worried about conflicts. or the possibility of the day being unproductive. or just generally a waste of everybody’s time. so far none of the workshops ive done have turned into a complete disaster although some could’ve gone better. now i still get nervous but just for the first 5 minutes then i morph into a workshop fiend.
.
it helped that i learned from every previous workshops i’ve done. i iterate on my workshop tool kit every chance i get. i copied things that i liked from other people. with pride. i dropped things that i tried that didnt work. with no remorse. i’ve learned to assume good intent (a phrase i’ve been hearing a lot lately) even when things werent exactly going as planned. and i listened to feedback given to me by managers and peers who had the unfortunate luck of having to be in my workshop. in the end it’s like developing new products. test. learn. iterate. what a nerd. but i love it now
.
the thing is my introvert self goes absolutely bonkers after every workshop i do. keeping the room focused and engaged to ensure a conclusion in the end is not easy for people like me who get drained from people-ing. at the end of the day, i spend what little energy i have left trying not to lock myself in the bathroom to be alone until i can stand the thought of having conversations again. welp. 😅
.
bonus: it doesn’t hurt that doing workshops in our paris office means getting treated to this view everytime we take a break. i always get the urge to break out into the entire les miserables song list whenever i am here. someday. one day.
.

__label__HoChiMinhCity,Vietnam no trunk, no problem. can you spot the 12 bags of rice/potato/magic that he's perfectly stacked on his motorbike? #lawdhammercy

just another everyday intersection where the streets of chaos and freedom collide.

motorbikes, cars, and people will be coming at you from every direction. so if you need to cross a street, only look straight ahead and just go for it.

if you stop or wait for someone to pass, you ironically mess up the flow of traffic. motorbikes are timing your movement ahead of time, so stopping only throws them off.

it takes a bit to get confident in this, but once you see how majestically they swerve and dodge pedestrians, you'll realize this is how they were taught to drive. and they're damn good at it!

vietnam is a country where everything just goes, and there's a beauty in this type of systematic chaos because somehow it's actually quite sustainable.

#busabout #busaboutvietnam #hochiminhcity #saigon #seasia

__label__HongKong what does freedom mean to you?

for some people it's a feeling, for others, it's a physical state of being.

i often jokingly talk about my very strict and sheltered nigerian upbringing, where i wasn't allowed to watch pg movies until i was 18, relationships were something you weren't allowed to have until you were married 🤔, and how you will very much fear the iron backhand of your mother well into your 50's.

but my definition of freedom is as literal as it gets, because i never got a taste of that in my youth, so i crave it every day now.

and it's probably why i get such itchy feet and love to constantly be on the move.

freedom exists on a spectrum though, rather than a form of an absolute.

breaking free from archaic and soul-crushing ideas of what success means in nigerian culture, is the current race i'm running now.

despite the tiresome trek, i recognize that this is freedom.

__label__Germany 🏰⚔️🛡this is my favorite view from a castle - so far 😉 we took this shot from the canon platform on the side of the castle 💣

_____________________________________________________

marksburg castle in braubach, germany is special for a few reasons... 1) it is part of the rhine river @unesco world heritage site; 2) it was used for defense (think of these castles as lookouts and toll booths on the river...if you watch @historyvikings you’ll know what i mean based on the season when they tried to capture francia); it is the only one along this river that wasn’t destroyed. 
_____________________________________________________

the tour is fantastic and you get to see the living quarters and kitchens...the beds were tiny, the toilets were literally holes in closets, and the fireplaces were huge.  the best part was walking up into the castle on the steep uneven stone driveway (?) ... horse-way i guess ... and imagining what it must have been like for anyone trying to charge the castle, or even returning home. as our tour guide said “horses didn’t live very long in those days, and neither did people which is why they drank so much”🙈😂
_____________________________________________________

i’ve never felt more like i was living in a fantasy world as i did on the rhine river.  more castles and cute towns on the way 🤴🏻👸🏻 @vikingcruises 
_____________________________________________________

__label__Goa,India just published my latest blog post - “if i were a season, i’d be monsoon” ☔️ read it at the link in my profile or on the-shooting-star.com ⛈
.
.
an excerpt:
“i lie on my back, floating alone in the pool, soft raindrops gently falling on my face. palm trees rustle in the breeze. a peacock cries in the distance. grey clouds move swiftly through the sky. i close my eyes and deeply inhale the heavy monsoon air, thinking that maybe, the clouds are erupting just to indulge me.
.
this is my season, the season i’d be if i were a season. this is the monsoon feeling i eagerly came back to india from cuba to chase…”
.
.
for the next few weeks, i’ll be chasing this feeling across india, in collaboration with @radissonrewards - starting with my fav part of the country in the rainy season, goa 👆🏼🌦🌴
.
.
go read the post, then tell me, if you were a season, which would you be? 🤔
.
.

__label__London,UnitedKingdom selamat pagi dari london! kalau ada temen teman yang ingin traveling ke uk (london, stonehenge, bath, manchester, liverpool, scotland dan lain lain) kami adalah anak anak indonesia yang menetap di london menawarkan jasa private bespoke tour (custom travel) dari mulai penjemputan, pembelian segala macam jenis tiket (dari transportasi sampai tiket  nonton bola di stadium, atraksi di seluruh uk), itinerary, private tour guide (sudah pasti orang indonesia) kendaraan dan supirnya, photographer (sama lah sama yang lagi happening sekarang2 ini hehe) bahkan ada jasa nanny hingga jasa bersih bersih airbnb kalian. intinya kami adalah bespoke tour, jadi menyesuaikan dengan kemauan kalian 😎 bisa ditanya langsung via dm ke saya. have a good day and hope to see you all in the uk! 🤗 #belokalondon #privatetourservices

__label__Bangkok,Thailand #tbt - i want to do a better job of sharing everyday life when i travel, in addition to those amazing landscapes and architectural marvels that are so famous. i thought i’d start with a photo i took at a night market on my most recent trip to thailand; one that shows why i love the city so very much. we all love different cities for different reasons and none of us have the same travel experience. i have a short list of cities i could return to a thousand times and never be bored and bangkok is near the top of that list. i honestly probably shouldn’t like bangkok as much as i do. my first trip there many years ago was also my first time visiting a so-called developing country. i still vividly remember walking out of the airport and being inundated by…everything. the smells, the wet air and the cacophony of people was all a lot to take. later during that same trip i was swindled by a fake tourist-cop, not the first time someone has been cheated in bangkok, but i was deeply shaken. i walked back to my hotel rom that evening in tears and vowed never to return. thankfully, that feeling was fleeting and within a day or so i was back out enjoying lunch at streets stalls and visiting temples and palaces. since then i’ve returned many times and as i said, today it’s a favorite place to spend some time. not to do or see any one thing, but just to be there, to enjoy the city for its intrinsic value. sometimes, that’s enough.

__label__YosemiteNationalPark continuing on with our #california national park exploration, next up is the iconic yosemite national park. i've photographed this park before and have always held a special place in my heart for it. yosemite is simply incredible. it's hard to imagine a more perfect natural setting for a park. my deep feeling for it also puts a burden on photographing it well...doing it the justice it deserves in the limited time we have in each park. but i am happy with the the images, stories, and experiences we had there and am excited to share some of them. let's start with a doozy.....the infamous taft point lookout. there never seems to be a shortage of people willing to risk life and limb for an epic photograph. luckily, i was there at the right time to capture it.

__label__Mexico ever since i started travel blogging over 7 years ago, there's a question that repeatedly pops up in my inbox. it is some version of this: "how do i convince my parents to let me travel?"
.
.
i know there was a time when travel was considered a luxury, an escape from everyday life; it was expensive, borders were closed, visas were difficult. but times have changed and how!
.
.
in this world that seems to be fearful of "foreigners", where all that we read about in the media breeds fear and hatred, it is more important now than ever to travel. because a school textbook can't describe the heartwarming hospitality of a traditional muslim family in jordan, or the proud and light-hearted spirit of ethiopians, or the egalitarian way of life in central america. fancy degrees might sound good to your friends, but real learning happens when you're stranded in a country you know nothing about, not even the language, and a kind stranger goes far out of his way to help you. even death - or the fear of it - acquires new perspective on the road.
.
.
no, travel is not a break from life. it is education in its truest, purest form. we need now, more than ever, for people to travel out of their comfort zones, to discover life beyond the cities and cubicles, to open up their world, to chase their dreams. we need less bankers and engineers, and more artists, musicians, writers, travellers, entrepreneurs, sportspeople, dreamers.
.
.
the above is an excerpt from an “open letter to indian parents” i wrote a while ago, on my blog. the full version is in my profile 😉
.
.
and you, have you had battles at home to let you travel / travel solo? .
.
ps: been almost a week since i flew to india from the uk, but the jet lag hasn’t gone. sleeping and waking up at the weirdest hours and not really thinking straight. think 🍺 could help? 🤔
.
.
photo —> throwback to mexico! how i miss that part of the world 🌎
.
.

__label__Moscow,Russia just having some me time ☺️ and i also have a very important ‼️message for you. after days of travelling in russia i can only conclude that unicorns and other members of the lgbt fauna are highly endangered species there. it must be traumatic for a unicorn to live in a society in which you may not exist. from my own experience i can assure you that it is horrific! i nearly got arrested multiple times for just being me. people started laughing with me or filming me in the middle of the streets, in the subway, ... some reported me to the closest police agent near me hoping i would get arrested.  i even got removed (without love) from the louis vuitton store in the world famous rym. just because i am a unicorn and thus inappropriate for their store. big shame on you louis vuitton. even my bff @els.goossens who stayed all those moments very close to me got enervated and tired by all the aggression towards me. i still remember a situation in which a girl wanted to ask me to take a picture of her and her lover, but that wasn’t alright for him. he wanted to beat her up for asking this to a unicorn. of course all of this was accompanied with a huge collection of insults towards me. 
it is really inhuman. i only had my eternal lioness smile as an answer towards this. on the other hand, the last day i learned that almost no one knows that it is for example forbidden for a unicorn to drive a car in russia. so i can only ask you to start supporting unicorns who are going through this every single day. they really deserve all your love! 💖💖💖🌈🌈🌈

__label__SouthernProvince,SriLanka often, when things don’t go the way we want them to, we feel bad and unmotivated because we limit our vision and perspectives on life. it is easy to complain and set yourself limits because we like to choose the “comfortable” or the “easy” way. but the best way to learn is to go beyond limits and set your own rules. being a person who spends a lot of time in my head and stress a lot about things, i am starting to learn that there is only so much we are in control of. sometimes you just have to take the seat on the swing and give it a little push. you will feel that feeling of freedom if you just trust your gut and let it all go ✨ thanks for capturing this wonderful moment @lucabagozza 💛

__label__Delhi,India perspective will take you further in life than any plane ticket ever will. this story will frustrate some of you, but i need to share it, because it’s a regular part of my travels.

india is a country of 1.3 billion people, and whenever i interact with locals, i always bear in mind that our exchange isn’t simply between two people.

i’m representing the entire black community, and since many indians have never met black people in person before, i anticipated some hesitation scattered between the smiles of adoration and selfies.

i walked to the elevator at my hotel in delhi and just a couple steps behind me was a family of 4. a mother, two teenaged sons, and a daughter.

the elevator arrived and i entered first and held my arm out - the universal gesture of “please enter." but the mother just stared. the sons awkwardly turned their backs. and the daughter, about 8 or 9 years old, made a small step forward that was met with a push back by her mother’s hand.

i did the indian head waggle (lol, my way of signaling that i come in peace) and motioned for them to come in.

the daughter again walked forward while the mother hesitantly followed, and eventually so did the two sons.

about a decade later, we arrived at the ground floor and i signaled with my arm for them to be let out first. tense, no one except the daughter made eye contact.

but don't blame india, this happens to me everywhere. on a packed bus when there is one seat left next to me, but people rather stand. or at the airport waiting rooms when i sit down and someone will get up and move away.

this is the life i chose. to expose myself to the realities of how black people are viewed globally. and to actively do the work of not only being a great representation of americans, but of black people altogether.

so i can no longer get upset by these interactions, because i don’t know what movie or rumor that mother heard about black people that made her feel like a two-story elevator ride with one wasn’t a risk she wanted to take.

it’s a humbling reminder as black people that we can smile, be friendly, and even speak a few words of the local language, yet still be subjected to the pigment of our skin. 💛

__label__Morocco sabah el kheir, morocco! this is my second time in this magnetic country and it's just as sensational and intoxicating as i remember it back in 2014.

morocco is a country of hustle and bustle, and though i came here solo last time, it's been so handy having a crew with me this time around.

moroccans are genuine and warm people, but if you can speak one of their languages (arabic or french), you'll get to experience the full extent of that warmth.

i "yala'd" and "habibi'd" my way through the medina, exchanging smiles, banter, and the all-too-familiar greetings of "mama africa!" and other unifying diaspora dialogue that always makes me smile.

marrakesh continues to be one of my favorite cities in the world because i live for its madness, chaos, and intensity.

one minute there's a donkey charging your way, the next a man is trying to hustle you wray pans (african ray bans 😅), all while you're dodging a couple hundred motorbikes a minute and resisting the temptation and beautiful assault of the spices and foods all around you.

charm, culture, and cuisine in one spot. marrakesh is life.

and it's countries like morocco that make me fall back in love with traveling, nomadic life, and getting to taste, breathe, and dance with some of the most enchanting cultures of the world.

المغرب، أنا أحبك!

__label__Paris,France ✨ caminar por parís es una experiencia hermosa, memorable y para nadie es un secreto lo fácil que es enamorarse de sus calles y edificios.
👉🏼 pero la parís actual no es la misma ciudad de la época medieval ni tampoco la misma del renacimiento.
👉🏼 el extraordinario cambio en el paisaje urbano tiene un único responsable: eugene haussmann.
👉🏼 urbanista y funcionario público al que le fue entregado el título de barón por parte de napoleon iii.
⚡️ la transformación de "la ciudad de la luz" fue llevada a cabo de 1852 a 1870.
👉🏼 tal cambio no fue únicamente buscando una estética moderna, ya que tenia un motivo más fuerte y específico: facilitar el movimiento de las tropas de napoleon iii para reprimir al pueblo si en algún momento surgía otra revolución como las que venían sucediendo en décadas anteriores.
💡 la dramática mutación efectuada por el barón consistió en:
• trasladados a los pobres a las zonas perifericas de parís.
• la place de charles de gaulle fue modificada con anchas vías en disposición radial a partir del arco del triunfo.
• se crearon numerosos espacios verdes, redes de agua y drenajes, y monumentos públicos.
• reglamentó que los edificios no debían superar los 20 metros a fin de darle uniformidad y modernidad a la ciudad.
• los edificios poseen un patrón particular que se compone de un gran balcón en el segundo piso (cuando está sobre los anchos boulevares), el tercero y cuarto piso tienen sólo ventanas y en el quinto tiene un balcón más sencillo.
• actualmente es común ver muchos de estos edificios sin ascensores y las escaleras en espiral pueden convertirse en una loca travesía dependiendo del piso en el que se viva. 😓
✨ así que la próxima vez que anden por estas lindas calles, recuerden el nombre del barón hausmann, el “poeta urbanista” de la capital de francia. 🧐
-

__label__Oregon who are you when no one’s looking? some of us run in a pack and some of us are lone wolves. spending time with friends and family is my favorite, but it’s times of solitude where you learn the most about yourself. where do your thoughts drift? what motivates you? how do you seek inspiration when others aren’t around pushing you? all questions i think about often when i’m looking up at the stars on a camping trip. being alone often carries a negative connotation in our society and is falsely tied to being lonely. being able to give yourself the gift of your own time is one of the most valuable things you can invest in.

__label__BurjKhalifa 🌍 location: dubai ~ uae (juny 2013)
---------------------------------------------------
burj khalifa (arabic: برج خليفة‎, "khalifa tower"), known as burj dubai prior to its inauguration, is a skyscraper in dubai, united arab emirates, and is the tallest man-made structure in the world, at 829.8 m (2,722 ft). construction began on 21 september 2004, with the exterior of the structure completed on 1 october 2009. the building officially opened on 4 january 2010,and is part of the new 2 km2 (490-acre) development called downtown dubai at the 'first interchange' along sheikh zayed road, near dubai's main business district. the tower's architecture and engineering were performed by skidmore, owings and merrill of chicago, with adrian smith as chief architect, and bill baker as chief structural engineer. the primary contractor was samsung c&t of south korea.

__label__LagunaBeach,California with a swell coming in mixed with some summer sunsets, it’s the perfect time to be home. they say the grass is always greener on the other side of the fence and that often sums up traveling for me. when i’m home i’m excited thinking of upcoming travel, but when i’m away i often long to come home. at the end of the day, it’s about being appreciative each morning you wake up and try to find joy in the present moment. it’s too easy to dwell on the past or worry about the future. teaching myself to be present in the moment has become something i’ve focused on a lot as i get older. each day is a chance to do something enjoyable for yourself. whether it’s waking up a little earlier and going on a morning walk, meeting up with a friend for coffee, or finding time to catch the sunset after work before you head home, you’ll be surprised how far a single act can go to improving your day.

__label__BuenosAires,Argentina this might look like just another plate of pizza but in actual fact this pizza is served as part of a very special intrepid buenos aires city tour. like so many intrepid products the ba city tour seeks to help local businesses and this tiny little kitchen is one such business. a small group of local women is working towards opening to the public and in the meantime they cater to intrepid groups providing hand made pizza, fresh salad and local delicacy empanadas. i'm so happy that intrepid are working with helloworld on my argentinian adventures. @helloworldau #expertsineverywhere

__label__Istanbul,Turkey coming to @ambientefair this friday, our bassa lamp is inspired by one of the 23 consonants of the ‘bassa vah’ alphabet.
.
.
bassa is a language still spoken today in parts of liberia and sierra leone but its alphabet fell out of use after being labeled a “failed script”, despite the formation of an association in 1959 for its promotion.
.
.
the name originates from the bassa word 'vah', meaning 'to throw a sign'. it is widely believed that the script developed from an earlier bassa communication system of signs made from chewed leaves which would then be carved into trees and left in set locations where they would be found and interpreted. as this system developed, it was employed to avoid slave traders and was therefore suppressed by colonial powers.
.
.
check out our website (link in bio) or scroll the feed for our furniture pieces inspired by other letters of the bassa alphabet ✍🏼

__label__Paris,France phone notification: “congratulations on your first sale!”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
me: “i got my first customer!!!!!!!!!!” i could hardly hold my emotions. i wanted to shout and laugh and dance…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i will never forget this moment  or the name of my very first customer. he was asking me to ship the pendant so that he could present it to his wife at the dinner on st. valentine’s day. i was so excited, i fedexed it. i didn’t care. all i wanted was for him to receive the design on time. i felt so humbled and wanted to make my customer happy.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
for you to understand how it felt, i have to explain (for those who don’t know) that i have been working towards this moment for 1 year! it is not just a sale. to me, it’s a confirmation of all my work and my goals… it’s my motivation to work even harder.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this moment was today.

__label__Bali,Indonesia when was the last time you experienced something so unusual you couldn’t help but... laugh?
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
last week, after i returned from visiting this epic waterfall, i was taking a shower in my villa’s outdoor bathroom (which, by the way, was amazing). halfway through my hot shower, it started torrentially pouring 😆 🌧 !
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
so here i was, standing butt naked in an outdoor shower in the middle of bali, getting drenched by hot water and freezing cold rain. i can’t say a sensory experience like that has ever happened to me.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
for a second, i was shocked at how i got sabotaged by the weather 😳, clueless as to what one does in that situation 🤷🏻‍♀️, and then i started laughing to myself like a crazy person.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
the moment was so delightful, unique, unexpected, and weird, that i just stood there under the stream of shower and rain water, cackling until my abs hurt 😂. does the shower even count if half of it was rain?!
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
it’s small, serendipitous memories like these that make me so grateful to be alive. do you have a unique memory that makes you smile?
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

over the past 6 years, our company have grown tremendously. we are in awe of our customers’ loyalty and their continuing support. consequently, we continue to work around the clock to identify and meet the needs of our customers. we have come to the realization that one of those needs are related to the financial challenges that come with planning a vacation, specifically when it comes to vacationing with a group. we want to make sure that no one is denied the ultimate vip vacation experience that we offer due to last minute planning or financial conflict.  for that reason,  the vip marketing & consulting firm has created the vmw membership program.

the membership program
vacay my way offers the opportunity to customize your own vip vacation experience by allowing you to accumulate small biweekly payments ($35, $50, or $75), that can be used towards any destination konpa in the next two years. this gives you control of your vacation without the stress of saving or organizing.  whether it’s a  solo or a group vacation, when vacationing with  destination konpa all you have to do is decide where you want to go to next.

__label__Bali,Indonesia i heard something recently that stuck with me: you can’t compare your inside to someone else’s outside. on this platform as with most social media, i’m sure it looks like there’s a lot of perfection in the lives of so many women who travel online, bolstered by strength and bravery that is somehow out of reach. but the truth is we all struggle, self-judge, and have our demons. it’s scary to share my inside, but i also think it’s important to be honest and raw, so with a deep breath, here it is: today marks one year since the last time i drank alcohol. i used to struggle with it while i traveled, while i climbed mountains, while i built my own business from nothing. it was there, a thorn in my side that i couldn’t remove until last july. i’m far from perfect, i really felt like the opposite for so long. since then life got better, i got stronger, my work became more meaningful and more of you came to be part of it and support me without even realizing that’s what you were doing. thank you for being here. thank you for being such a big inspiration to me. thank you for every uplifting comment and message. you mean so much to me.

i wrote a post about how i transitioned and what changed in my life since i did. i hope that if it’s what you need to read today, that it reaches you somehow. cheers to strength, humility, and gratitude 🙏 and to another year with a new lease on life.

__label__CapeTown,WesternCape fun fact: i absolutely love heights.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
skydiving, hot air ballooning, planes, paragliding, you name it - the higher up in the sky and the more open air, the better.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
i was 3 months old the first time i was on a plane, and my god, i have loved the feeling ever since.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
everything about flying unravels me: i am enamored by that feeling of limitless freedom, like all the possibilities in the world are at my fingertips.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
when i’m in the sky, i can go anywhere and see the world beneath me… and the best part is, the world can’t see me. it’s simply comforting.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
this is a shot of my paragliding near cape town, south africa! it was my first time and it was magic ✨!! 10 whole minutes high up in the air, not the same rush as skydiving but definitely appreciated the chill airborne time.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
does anyone else love flying like i do? if not, what’s your passion hobby?

__label__MainBeach well i am home for the next 2 1/2 weeks catching up on things and i’ve got lots of exciting news to share! for example, i just had my fifth @thetravelbootcamp conference here on the gold coast and it was an incredible success. i’ve also reopened the cart for my online photography course and you can check it out via my bio now. __label__Iceland iceland - zauber von feuer und eis ❄️ *zuhause* welche mæchtiges wort!
wie dieses kleine hæuschen  in dieser rauchen / zerklüfteten und wunderbar anmutenden natur. so soll auch dein zuhause eine festung sein, welches den winden und den gewalten von außen stand hælt. dir geborgenheit geben soll und dir zuflucht gibt in situationen wo dir der mut ein wenig fehlen mag. schau wer die bewohner deines hauses sind - welche energie lassen sie dir zukommen. 
nur ein gesundes und stabiles haus 🏡 gibt dir den schutz und die ruhe wieder deine stärke zu finden. nur wenn du dich ausruhen und fallen lassen kannst wirdt du dich wieder sammeln und aufladen können. schuss wer die bewohner sind - ob ihr euch ergænzt und nicht blockiert / wie gut ihr euch tut und welche wunderbare welt ihr euch um euer haus erbaut. 👁‍🗨 was schätzt du an deinem „hæuschen“ / was ist deine dankbarkeit wenn du an dein umfeld denkst.

#icelandtravel #icelandscape

vielen dank für deine zeit und solltest du mir ein like oder sogar einen kommentar hier lassen, dann freut es mich wenn dich meine arbeit anspricht.
sei gegrüßt und schön, wenn du wieder vorbeischauen würdest ;) thx a lot

__label__Venice,Italy i just want to take a moment to thank you guys for the love and support from my latest blog post.

as i said, the words were harsh, but necessary. it resonated with most, and struck a nerve with others, and that's completely okay.

took a couple days to catch up, but the amount of emails from people opening up their homes to me around africa brought me to tears.

that, and other travelers sharing their stories of also feeling disconnected from their home towns after opening up their mind to the lessons of the world.

it's a hard place to be. loving and cherishing the people from your past, but knowing there's limited space/patience for them in your future.

it doesn't mean you need to cut people out of your life. you can continue to support and wish them well from afar.

what you do need to do though, is foster new relationships that grow, challenge, and develop the person you're meant to be.

stagnancy is regression in my book. and if i'm not learning something new every day, i'm wasting precious time.

i've always said people aren't inspired by perfection, they're inspired by transparency.

so i will continue to share the raw, the real, and the gritty of my heart, because that's the only way i know how to write.

again, my platform isn't here to coddle your privilege or comfort your ego.

it is so nice to be in a mental space where you feel so confident about the direction of your life. 
this will excite most and intimidate others. luckily, the only approval i need is mine and the man upstairs.

here's to new beginnings and those open to growing with me | link in bio for those who'd like to read the blog post in question ❤

__label__GlacierNationalPark when my alarm is set for 3am it typically means it's going to be a good day. i didn't really know what to expect as we raced across @glaciernps to catch the sunrise. our only goal was to explore sun up till sun down to celebrate the 100th birthday of the parks. we started at swiftcurrent lake & ended at bowman lake. during those 19 hours we ate copious amounts of huckleberry goods, hiked, cliff jumped, swam, kayaked and basically just sat there with our jaws on the ground at the beauty of this place. 😱
.
@instagram asked if they could share an ig story from my day. check it out later today on their feed.
.
ps - i'll be at the instameet tonight at lake mcdonald with @glaciernps - 6pm👌🏼

__label__Oregon i spent the first few days of 2018 with some of my favorite people down in oregon. we hiked, cooked, hung out in hot springs, played some heated rounds of taboo, and stayed up late sharing stories around the fireplace. it was an amazing reminder of how important it is to surround ourselves with people that reflect who we want to be and how we want to feel. energies are contagious! and i’m excited to be leaving our little cabin in the woods motivated to be more, create more, and share more, in the new year. -

__label__JoshuaTreeNationalPark so, i was debating posting this photo because it felt too revealing... i was scared of all the people who would make creepy comments about my body, objectify me, or dm with some sort of disgusting message (it's happened). and then i realized how screwed up it is that this is even a concern.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
in light of recent political events - where the fate of women's bodies have been, once again, predominantly put into the hands of bigoted men in power - i decided to post this anyway. i refuse to partake in a society where i have to apologize for being revealing, too sexy, or for being the way i was made.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
this is me, this is my body, it is beautiful, artistic, and i have every right in the world to share it without having to fear repercussions.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
outwardly inappropriate comments will be featured on my stories for the world to see that we unfortunately still live in a society full of objectifiers and shamers. women don't deserve to live in fear of predators. so for all you men out there who respect and treat us like equals - and for all the women who support and strengthen each other - thank you ❤️.

__label__Paris,France the other day instagram sent me a survey with questions such as whether instagram is good for the world 🙄
•
there’s a lot of criticism of influencers here promoting materialistic lifestyles by showing off expensive hotels, constant unboxing, or rooms so full of shoes that you could probably dress an entire village in them.
•
however, this trend and people being interested in seeing it isn’t just a side effect of instagram. •
if you go to the louvre (since this photo is from paris) and see paintings from let’s say for instance baroque era, a lot of them are either portraits of rich people, still life of fancy objects or food, or genre scenes from events. because there was a demand for it. •
how many painters showed off peasants or servants? very few. and those who did focus on authenticity like for instance my favorite vermeer died poor and in huge debt. •
i don’t think we, as humans, changed that much - we have curiosity in things most of us can’t have, such as expensive stuff. •
we just need to remember that the art/creations we see here in photos aren’t always people’s real lives - clothes can be rented, getting to the perfect spot can take forever, and some bloggers staying in luxury hotels might actually be lonely and broke. • 
for example, today i spent the day on a couch in my pajamas eating haribo gummy bears (turns out they’re great for clearing a blocked nose, lol!). 😉

__label__ChiangMai,Thailand my ideal sunday funday 😻 clearly this rescue elephant appreciated my mad mud mask making skills on her, because she kept randomly hugging me and humming! ...and also reciprocating the mud mask on my entire body. 🧖🏽‍♀️🐘💁‍♀️

__label__ChiangMai,Thailand and just like that, สวัสดี thailand! first stop, chiang mai. say hello to my newest friend, but he really only cares for endless piles of fruit! i think we’ll be friends for life. 🍌🍉🍇🍓 i’ve always wanted to visit elephants, but known that in the tourism trade, the elephant business can be highly unethical and the treatment of elephants is usually very poor. with many ‘sanctuaries’ claiming to look after and treat elephants (but actually doing the complete opposite) it’s hard to know if any place exists to actually care for these creatures. i put a fair amount of research into which spot was the best one to visit, and read many blogs and online reviews before deciding to visit elephant nature park in chiang mai. here, about 70 elephants roam and are looked after, and most have been rescued from the elephant riding business. there is no riding of elephants, no hooks or sticks in sight, and you may only approach to feed the elephants if you are advised to do so. but most likely the elephants come straight for you if you have bananas. 🙈 these beautiful and highly intelligent creatures pretty much exist to eat and sleep (we were told they eat for 16 hours a day) and that’s exactly what they get to do here. ❤️🐘

__label__Australia do you have any tattoos?
____________________________________
i get asked by you guys for my tattoos a lot, and despite not being a person that enjoys sharing them or their meaning, i feel like i owe it to you after so many q&as ignoring the subject:

1. three tibetan words on my upper right back. my first tattoo! got it when i was 23.
2. “happiness is only real when shared” in sinhalese on my left dorsal.
3. number 27 on my upper right triceps. my bday, which ive celebrated 70% of the last decade abroad.
4. r, viking rune. means “journey” and is also and r, for my last name.
5. eternal lotus. got it in bhutan and represents eternal love. do you remember my stories from that day?
6. captain’s insignia on my left shoulder. got it in bali last month. represents my favorite poem: “i am the master of my fate, i am the captain of my soul”.
7. k’aaxil: means wild in mayan. did it together with my friends in mexico. the artist messed it up and i’ll probably cover it next month in polynesia.
____________________________________
how about you? what tattoos do you have and what do they mean?

__label__Morocco most of the meat you'll enjoy in morocco is free-range, antibiotics-free, all raised on a steady diet of grass and wild herbs. that is why the lamb and mutton are so my much flavourful in morocco! .

la plupart des viandes que vous apprécierez au maroc sont en liberté, sans antibiotiques, toutes nourries d'herbe et d'herbes sauvages. c'est pourquoi l'agneau et le mouton sont tellement mon savoureux au maroc! .

la mayor parte de la carne que disfrutará en marruecos es de campo abierto, libre de antibióticos, todos criados con una dieta constante de hierba y hierbas silvestres. ¡es por eso que el cordero y el cordero son tan sabrosos en marruecos! .

您在摩洛哥享用的大部分肉類都是自由放養的，不含抗生素，所有這些都是在草和野草藥的穩定飲食下飼養的。這就是為什麼羊肉和羊肉在摩洛哥非常美味！ .

__label__Santorini for those who started following me in the middle of my journey or even recently, and you're wondering how i fell into this crazy lifestyle, i finally come clean - i have a sugar daddy!

hahaha, jk. we can't all be so lucky in life (jk again 😂). but i was just featured on a podcast that recaps my last 4 years, all the way from when i took my first international trip which opened my eyes to a world where i honestly didn't think "my kind" could fit in (listen to understand what i mean by that). 30 countries later, i fought to figure out the balance between what pays my bills and what fuels my passions.

i always say to hustle until your passion becomes your paycheck and words can't describe the feeling of finally achieving that. the world has become my black-sanded beach (photo: perissa beach on santorini island). i hope this inspires someone and thank you, @tranekaenespana for having me!

podcast link: bit.ly/travelwithglo

__label__HongKong this week i’ve spent a lot of time making travel plans for the year, trying to decide where i want to go and when. a place i’m likely to return to (for the third year in a row) is one that has slowly endeared itself to me - hong kong.

when i think of the word frenetic, hong kong usually is the first image that pops into my head. it’s a curious place, intensely modern with skyscrapers, technology and a bustling population that never seems to stop. but it’s not all modernity and flashing lights, there’s still a traditional side of hong kong to be found and luckily it’s not hidden or tucked away as in some cities. no, hong kong fuses modern life with tradition in a way that’s rare but somehow makes perfect sense when you visit. sure, you can visit the genius bar in the massive apple store, but then you can grab a meal on the go at any of the gazillion street vendors around town, making classic meals in the same way it’s been done for decades. maybe that’s what i like best about the city, it’s ability to constantly move forward without losing sight of the values and traditions at the root of its culture.

hong kong has had a very strange history and around town it’s reflected in every way imaginable. for generations the city has been a global crossroads, which it remains today. you’ll hear every language imaginable and people from every corner of the world, all coexisting and all becoming part of the city’s pulsating matrix. it’s an addictive city, one that begs you to go back for more and i can’t wait to do just that in a few months, to stuff my face silly with all of the amazing food but also to pick up a few more stories from a city that has millions to tell.

__label__Lisbon,Portugal when i first visited lisbon seven years ago, i wasn’t terribly impressed. i found that it was lacking a je ne sais quoi: it wasn’t as edgy or eccentric as i like my cities to be, and so i left wanting more.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
this time around, though, my experience was completely different. at first i thought it was because i was the one who changed (which is also true), but i’ve also learned that the city has transformed in the past few years.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
with the recent influx of tourism, lisbon has come alive: neighborhoods are developing, digital nomads are flocking over, and it’s becoming a truly cosmopolitan city. of course there are consequences to this (too many tourists, gentrification, etc), but from what i’ve seen, it has mostly evolved the city. so i changed my mind: i now love lisbon.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
have you had this happen to you - that you totally loved/hated something and then when you revisited, you’ve found that your opinion changed? would love to hear your thoughts in the comments below 👇🏼.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
huge thank you to @traveling_to_portugal, an amazingggg travel company who showed me everything there was to know about lisbon! highly recommend them to anyone who visits!
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

__label__Stockholm,Sweden the way i judge a city's progressiveness is through their elderly population and i was pleasantly surprised to learn that the most talkative of the swedish bunch, lies in the older demographic.

i was getting some groceries at the store and a woman came up to me and said how pretty my dress was, and how it made her smile.

a feeble man welcomed me on the metro and shared a couple of his favorite restaurants.

also, whenever they approach me, they always speak in swedish, which i actually appreciate because it's a sign that they're aware and accepting that someone of my ethnic background could have been born and raised here.

again, stockholm is incredibly diverse. way more diverse than other big cities like barcelona, athens, or dublin.

i keep finding myself in awkward situations (like yesterday) but i'm learning how to just mind my business 😅 #sohard

a taxi pulled off with a woman passenger and her suitcase in the trunk, except he forgot to close the trunk.

i waved my hands and hollered for him to stop, but he didn't see me. the rest of stockholm did, though. and like yesterday's situation, they saw the situation but didn't feel the need to say anything.

the bystander effect (google this, very relevant) is prominent, and while it's not how i'm used to living, it was a culture shock to try and adapt it for a few days to blend in with everyone else.

but man, once they get some alcohol in them, they're like an open book.

sweden is part of what they call the "vodka belt" along with the other nordic and baltic countries, and of course russia.

public drinking, unlike copenhagen, is forbidden, so i made sure my flask wasn't in plain view 😌

alcohol over 3.5% can only be purchased at licensed restaurants and bars, not at liquor stores like in most countries.

over a century ago, they even had to carry around a book that tracked their alcoholic consumption per month. such interesting laws that obviously died over time but may be telling of their drinking culture today.

stockholm, overall, was a nice change of pace, but now i'm ready for the norwegian beauty up north!

let the good times with @eurail continue!
#createyourownstory 📖✏️🚄🚉

__label__Petra,Ma`An,Jordan древний город петра 🏛 ⠀ ⠀
⠀
👽 загадочный и необычный скальный город, про который находили время писать мудрецы древности. на местном языке оно получило название села, что означает камень. позже греки перевели «камень» в «петра», в таком виде название города дошло и до наших времен. ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀
🗺 дорога в скальный город петра начинается с узкого ущелья, вдоль которого с двух сторон возвышаются на сотни метров скалы. движение происходит в темноте, солнце не может попасть сюда. дальше постепенно начинает светлеть, и становятся заметными вырубленные в скале ниши для статуй. ⠀ ⠀
⠀
🤔 загадкой остается и то, как же все-таки строители вырезали здание в храме. как правило, в таких случаях нужно сооружать строительные леса, но деревьев в этом районе не было. оставалось лишь, пользуясь развалами в скале, забираться наверх и начинать работу оттуда. при этом неизвестно как рабочим удавалось трудиться на большой высоте «на весу», неизвестно также и как они оценивали размеры и масштабы будущей постройки. ⠀
⠀ ⠀ ⠀
😍 в настоящее время это место привлекает тысячи туристов, желающих погрузиться в атмосферу древнего скального зодчества и стать свидетелями великих произведений искусства. ⠀
⠀

__label__GrandCanyonNationalPark the grand canyon is so many things to so many people. at the rim, it's a madhouse of people, busses, activity.....and, of course, some of the most amazing views of any national park in the world. but get down below the rim, into the canyon, and it's as if you stumbled upon a peaceful secret. the crowds thin, the only noise you hear are birds and the mighty rushing colorado river (which formed this canyon), and this magical light that makes everything seem like a fantasyland shines so bright. what a joy to have experienced the infamous rim to rim hike in the grand canyon. my muscles ached, but my heart soared like the condors who call this amazing place home

__label__Utah i wanted to share this months ago, but the experience hadn’t fully set in for me yet. flying through a storm cell in an open cockpit plane ranks pretty high on my list of the most uncomfortable experiences of 2017, but also the most beautiful ... truly. the desert was dappled in sunlight as heavy clouds sent down rain, we could even smell the petrichor rise up as the rain fell on dry soil. .

but in an instant all that beauty kinda faded away as i tucked my camera in my jacket when we realized there was no avoiding this storm. it had encircled us. the cockpit of the small trike started to shake as i could feel tiny drops of rain hit my helmet.. joyful for a second until the heavy rain started to hit. it felt like small nails hitting every part of my exposed skin. hands got shoved in my jacket and head went down as wind & rain overtook us for a brief moment.
.

it felt like a car accident waiting to happen. upon exiting we realized that we were too close & would have to elevate to avoid the others... so still damp we took the aircraft to 12k+ feet & i basically started to freeze. completely unprepared for this 40 minute flight (turned multiple hours)  from monument valley to hanksville i was shivering barely in control. .

there is no room to shake your feet or legs in the cockpit without exposing them to wind, rain or freezing temps. we made a quick descent over the mtns & went back into sunshine where the black asphalt runway provided ample temps to bring my feet & hands back to life. i love when an experience has the ability to simmer a bit. often for me it takes writing it down & thinking on it a bit. thanks @shotsfromabove for keeping us safe on this one.

__label__India my year 2018 , thank you guys for giving this overwhelming response.
in less then 24 hours 1000 comments are there on this video, i want to thank you for this love .
now behind the making :
this video took me 15 days to complete the edit, 
first of all i went to manali shot the video came back, with story telling footage about the year.
but i felt like i want to make this video with a different approach.
i sat down started looking for music then i recalled the time, when i had watched watch tower of turkey, when first time i saw that, i was like dude this is above my imagination, i want to do something like that one day, and i forgot this.
and when again i saw this , i realized yes why not now, i have shot so many footage of 2018 , i have been to mountains, beaches, desserts, hill stations in short i have travelled a lot.
why not to make this happen now.
took whole day to say yes to myself for the idea .
and from then in 15 days, i was editing almost everyday, i used to edit till 5-6 am in the morning without sleeping in night then i used to sleep in day so that in night i have that peace to imagine and create.
.
.

after 8-9 days i reached at edit of 2 minutes 
but i was not happy i deleted whole sequence and restarted with new approach
.
.
trust me there was a time when my friends, family, subsribers everyone was just asking me "how much more time you need" ?
and my answer used to be " i don't know "

800gb data, hundreds of footage , 
content  from over indian destinations 
and one 4 minutes video.
finally yesterday got over with edits and gave you bruh, to post 1000 comments on video.
i thought it will take 6-7 days meanwhile i will start editing new masterpiece from maldives but what ???
one day , just one day and it's done.
i'm so convinced that quality matters in content cause it impacts.
thanks bruh, for love and support.
tommorow trailer will be up on youtube .

__label__California we finally have a smart home! over the past month we’ve been replacing our standard dimmers with caséta by @lutronelectronics dimmers. there are all sorts of great features with the dimmers, and i’ll talk about the travel-related ones over the next month, but my favorite thing so far is that i’m notified if i drive away from the house and there are any lights on. my kids leave their lights on virtually every morning after getting ready for school, and especially now that it’s so dark in the mornings, i do too. no more coming back home several hours later to find all of the lights on – and using electricity. now i get the notification, and as soon as i stop driving, can go into the app and turn off all of the lights that are on. brilliant! 
#sponsored #casetasmartlighting #familytravel #smarthome

__label__NewYork,NewYork a few weeks ago, i posted some ig stories of me getting a tattoo, but i didn’t show you what it was 😉. well, here it is! this lovely piece of ink actually means the world to me (lol, see what i did there), and i wanted to explain why to those who are interested:
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
one of my favorite quotes of all-time is from the book cloud atlas and it goes, “my life amounts to no more than one drop in a limitless ocean. yet what is any ocean, but a multitude of drops?”
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
these words beautifully represent a life paradox that i subscribe to: we are nothing and everything at the same time. it’s hard to accept, but it's quite possible that every action that we take in our lifetime will be forgotten. in the grand scheme of things, our minuscule existence represents little more than a drop in the ocean.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
even so… our actions do have consequences. every action we take has a ripple effect somewhere in the world. we can’t possibly predict who our actions will impact or inspire, but rest assured that someone out there will be affected by your decisions.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
the real question is - what do you want to make of this life? do you want to live it solely for yourself, or do you also want to contribute to the well-being of the planet during your short time here?
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
collectively, everything we do matters, but only if we are each chipping in our part to contribute to the whole of humanity. together, we are as powerful as the ocean.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
this tattoo represents two ends of the spectrum: i want to honor my responsibility in this world, while staying humble to my insignificance. would love to hear your thoughts on this below 👇🏼.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
